%% WG packet flow: NSC -> NSGW UDP:51820 -> NSN
%% Source: tests/docker/nsgw-mock/entrypoint.sh + traefik-config.ts + crates/tunnel-wg/
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant NSC as NSC (gotatun user-space)
    participant NSGW_WG as NSGW wg0 (kernel)
    participant NSGW_TRA as NSGW traefik :443
    participant NSGW_FWD as NSGW kernel forward
    participant NSN_WG as NSN gotatun (user-space)
    participant NSN_SR as NSN ServiceRouter
    participant SVC as Real service :80

    Note over NSC,SVC: Case A - Direct WG (NSC sends to NSN virtual IP via wg0)
    NSC->>NSGW_WG: UDP :51820 WG packet<br/>(peer=NSC pubkey, payload dst=10.0.0.2)
    NSGW_WG->>NSGW_WG: decrypt + verify<br/>allowed-ips check (src)
    NSGW_WG->>NSGW_FWD: plaintext IP (dst=10.0.0.2)
    NSGW_FWD->>NSGW_FWD: route lookup<br/>10.0.0.2 -> wg0 peer=NSN
    NSGW_FWD->>NSGW_WG: encap to NSN peer
    NSGW_WG->>NSN_WG: UDP :51820 WG packet
    NSN_WG->>NSN_SR: decap + dispatch virtual_port
    NSN_SR->>SVC: TCP connect 127.0.0.1:80

    Note over NSC,SVC: Case B - HTTPS via traefik (browser -> Host app.example.com)
    NSC->>NSGW_TRA: TCP :443 TLS ClientHello<br/>SNI app.example.com
    NSGW_TRA->>NSGW_TRA: TLS terminate (default cert)
    NSGW_TRA->>NSGW_TRA: router match Host()<br/>service -> http://10.0.0.2:10000
    NSGW_TRA->>NSGW_FWD: TCP connect 10.0.0.2:10000 (plaintext)
    NSGW_FWD->>NSGW_WG: encap (dst in NSN allowed-ips)
    NSGW_WG->>NSN_WG: UDP :51820 WG packet
    NSN_WG->>NSN_SR: decap + dispatch virtual_port 10000
    NSN_SR->>SVC: TCP connect 127.0.0.1:80
    SVC-->>NSN_SR: HTTP response
    NSN_SR-->>NSGW_TRA: (encrypted path reversed)
    NSGW_TRA-->>NSC: HTTPS response
